TEACHER.observations: I started by looking at the map so we both understood there was a new shape. I then drew a square with a triangle in it as best I could. When she did the maps I had to go back and draw a 1, so she knew to only press one. I think we communicated well and both did a good job, I would not have done anything differently.

TEACHER.observations: I this one I only drew a triangle, knowing she would try to press all, but cut her off each time she tried to touch the last one. This worked fairly quickly, and she caught on not to press the last one. I think we both did a good job, and I would not have done anything differently.

43.task: Touch exactly one object that is [partially but not all] blue.

STUDENT.observations: It was extremely frustrating at some points in the experiment, especially when there was trouble understanding my partner.

4.comment: Use the car (thick arrow) to trace out messages in its path.

STUDENT.guess: Touch 1 object that if half blue.

TEACHER.observations: I think it was hard for me to understand any symbols she was trying to use because I had no basis for what she might try to write. I feel like feedback from her would more likely be complex because it would indicate confusion, but it was more clear that what I was showing would be something found in one of the statements which are limited to number/quantifiers, colors, shapes, and size. It was sometimes frustrating (especially writing 3) and there were a few times where I would teach to the best I understood the statement, but it still ended up being wrong which I couldn't correct, so it would have been nice to possibly have more examples for the teacher beforehand.
